# Svelte 5 + SvelteKit 2

## Runes (required in this project)

```svelte
<script lang="ts">
	let { title, count = 0 }: { title: string; count?: number } = $props();
	let doubled = $derived(count * 2);
	let items = $state<string[]>([]);
</script>

<button onclick={() => items.push('x')}>{title}: {doubled}</button>
```

- Use `$props()`, `$state`, `$derived` / `$derived.by` — not `export let`, `$:`, or legacy `on:click`
- Event handlers: `onclick`, `onsubmit` (not `on:click`)
- Children: `let { children } = $props()` and `{@render children()}`
- Props-derived values must use `$derived`, not plain `let`

## SvelteKit 2 client APIs

```ts
import { page } from '$app/state';
import { enhance } from '$app/forms';
import { resolve } from '$app/paths';
```

- Navigation/state: `$app/state`, not `$app/stores`
- Links: `resolve('/path')` for type-safe hrefs
- Forms: `use:enhance` with `+page.server.ts` actions

## Avoid

- `$effect` for derived state (use `$derived`)
- `browser` guards inside `$effect` (effects don't run on server)
- Legacy slots (`<slot>`) — use snippets instead

Use the Svelte MCP `svelte-autofixer` when writing or editing `.svelte` files.
